<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}-{2}{y}={90}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}-{9}{y}={33}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({8},-{9}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --6. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{6}}{{9}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{6}}}{{9}}{\left({9}{x}+-{2}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{6}}}{{9}}{\left({90}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{6}\right)}{x}+-{1.3333333333333}{y}={60}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}-{9}{y}={33}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{10.333333333333}{y}={93}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{93}}{{-{{10.333333333333}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{9}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+-{2}{\left(-{9}\right)}={90}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{\left({18}\right)}={90}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}={90}-{\left({18}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}={72}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{72}}{{9}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={8}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({8},-{9}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

